    value: 궁궐의 가장 높은 곳
  - key: '[주-D001] 月山君 : '
    value: 저본에는 없다. 저본의 원목차에 근거하여 보충하였다.
english:
  title: Twelve-Rhyme Poem on Snow Within the Forbidden Palace
  author: Lee Jeong
  language: eng
  text: |-
    The north wind howls and will not cease,
    While dawn snow dances left and right.
    With cunning grace it pierces window panes,
    On dangerous wings it strikes the roof's ridge.
    First freezing, the clouds remain unbroken,
    Sleet gathers in silence without sound.
    Cold air invades the halls of splendor,
    Frost light leaks through the painted pillars.
    The moon should surely contest its brightness,
    While plum blossoms jealously guard their purity.
    The radiance shines on the golden palace,
    Misty and dim, it blurs the jade towers.
    The highest eaves are buried then revealed,
    The celestial gates grow dark, then bright again.
    So I glimpse the coming of prosperous years,
    And see good fortune manifest this day.
    When its season arrives, the old plagues melt away,
    What thing would not send forth new growth?
    The officials gathered in court give their praise aloud,
    While joy rises and common folk dance in the fields.
    Flying crows cry out in their own delight,
    And ancient trees lean together as they stand.
    But who could have foreseen that after the snow clears,
    Severe cold would arrive to torment us at the wine cup?
